{
  "texts": [
    "Forty years was selected as a cut-off age, following recommendations by the US Multi-Society Task Force, which recommends screening at age 45 years for average-risk patients and screening at age 40 years in persons with a family history of CRC [32].To ensure active patients in this sample, we subset patients who had:• At least 2 codes (procedural or diagnostic) within 3 years of each other.",
    "• At least one clinical note with the social history section (social history section was detected and extracted from clinical notes using regular expressions, two examples of social history section can be found in Supplement A).The patients were marked as screened for CRC if they had one of the following codes:• General screening code (ICD-10-CM Z12.11).• Colonoscopy (CPT 45378, CPT 45379, CPT 45380, CPT 45381, CPT 45385, CPT 1022231, HCPCS G0121, HCPCS G0120, HCPCS G0105).",
    "• Sigmoidoscopy (CPT 1007635, HCPCS G0104).",
    "• Occult blood test (CPT 82270, CPT 82274, CPT 82272, HCPCS G0328).",
    "• DNA test (CPT 81528, LOINC 77354-9)."
  ]
}